WEBVTT

00:00.226 --> 00:03.190
And I want to do a little bit like we did last week.

00:03.211 --> 00:05.754
We talked Sunday from James.

00:06.055 --> 00:11.824
I don't know that I'll do this every week, but I think there are some things that are really important for us to get a hold of.

00:12.925 --> 00:15.028
So last week, leading ourself into joy.

00:15.048 --> 00:19.195
That's so critical that we develop that in our life.

00:19.796 --> 00:22.139
And then we talked Sunday about temptation.

00:22.159 --> 00:25.865
And I want to talk to you about the goodness of God.

00:27.067 --> 00:29.330
Because when it comes to

00:29.506 --> 00:30.407
temptation.

00:30.447 --> 00:38.159
The root of temptation is the thought that somehow we know better than God what will make us happy.

00:40.122 --> 00:58.450
And so rather than trust him to provide the good and the perfect gifts that he would want to provide, we can have a tendency to take matters in our own hands or we can forget about the things he's provided and as a result find ourselves in a place of temptation.

00:59.586 --> 01:10.479
So in James chapter one and verse 16, don't be deceived, my dear brothers, every good and perfect gift is from above.

01:11.700 --> 01:20.130
Coming down from the Father of the heavenly lights, who does not change like shifting shadows.

01:22.093 --> 01:26.578
God wants to do good in our life.

01:27.522 --> 01:32.091
I don't know whether you've settled in your heart, but God is good and He does good.

01:32.131 --> 01:40.407
And He delights in sending into our lives good and perfect gifts.

01:41.388 --> 01:44.454
So I want to give you just three thoughts about the goodness of God.

01:44.514 --> 01:48.562
Number one, we have to guard the goodness of God in our hearts.

01:49.378 --> 01:54.343
We have to constantly remind ourselves that God is good.

01:54.804 --> 02:02.372
I think that's exactly why James says in verse 16, don't be deceived, my dear brothers.

02:03.694 --> 02:09.340
Temptation comes because we believe something about God that is not true.

02:10.261 --> 02:18.930
Now I want you to think about this because back at the beginning, the very first couple to be tempted, Adam and Eve, here's what happened in the garden.

02:19.554 --> 02:25.883
The serpent said, God knows that your eyes will be opened as soon as you eat the fruit.

02:27.225 --> 02:31.451
And you will be like God knowing both good and evil.

02:31.892 --> 02:33.194
That's a lie.

02:33.594 --> 02:42.928
And what he is implying is he is saying, listen, the reason why God doesn't want you to eat that fruit is because he's afraid you'll be like him.

02:42.968 --> 02:47.474
And he's holding something good from you.

02:47.842 --> 02:50.145
And that's why you got to look out for yourself.

02:50.485 --> 02:56.773
And that's why you're going to want to eat the fruit because God is just, he's just petty, he's just insecure.

02:56.854 --> 02:58.676
He doesn't really care about you.

02:58.716 --> 03:00.538
He only cares about himself.

03:00.899 --> 03:01.419
And you know what?

03:01.499 --> 03:04.784
You just need to do what you think is best for you.

03:04.824 --> 03:09.670
That same lie is the lie that the world is being sold today.

03:09.710 --> 03:16.018
The devil has not changed in thousands of years.

03:17.250 --> 03:18.712
You know what's interesting to me?

03:18.752 --> 03:32.112
How many Christians are susceptible to the lie that God isn't good and that he doesn't want to do good in people's lives?

03:33.354 --> 03:34.175
You think about it.

03:34.456 --> 03:36.639
How many times have you heard Christians?

03:36.699 --> 03:38.101
I'm not talking about nine Christians.

03:38.502 --> 03:46.514
I'm talking about Christians who rail against the idea that God wants to bless people and God does bless people.

03:47.746 --> 03:49.428
It's a very interesting thing.

03:49.468 --> 03:57.637
There is a whole stream in Christianity that says God isn't good.

03:57.657 --> 03:58.759
He wants us to suffer.

04:01.021 --> 04:05.186
I'm not saying suffering is not a part of life.

04:05.226 --> 04:08.730
Man is born to trouble as surely as the sparks fly upward.

04:10.292 --> 04:15.698
But I also know this, that God is a deliverer and God promises

04:15.842 --> 04:18.482
to work in our life and to do good.

04:19.362 --> 04:23.166
And when it comes to temptation, the enemy rarely starts with the sin.

04:23.226 --> 04:27.731
He starts with the story and the story is usually, God isn't good.

04:27.771 --> 04:29.433
God can't be trusted.

04:29.774 --> 04:33.258
Remember that time you asked God to do something and He didn't come through for you.

04:33.578 --> 04:34.179
So you know what?

04:34.459 --> 04:35.560
It doesn't always work.

04:35.841 --> 04:37.042
Prayer doesn't always work.

04:37.362 --> 04:39.044
God doesn't always answer prayer.

04:39.865 --> 04:41.807
He's not always gonna come through for you.

04:41.867 --> 04:47.794
And some people go so far, sometimes the enemy goes so far as to say God doesn't care at all.

04:49.346 --> 04:57.061
And we have to guard our hearts, we have to guard our minds, and we have to believe that God is a good God.

04:58.624 --> 05:12.210
And if a person doesn't start there believing for the impossible, believing God for big things, believing for miracles will be very, very difficult if you don't believe that God is a good God.

05:13.090 --> 05:14.252
settle it in your heart.

05:14.512 --> 05:16.315
He's good and he wants to do good.

05:16.635 --> 05:19.339
He'll be better to you than you'd be to yourself.

05:19.719 --> 05:21.762
God desires to work in your life.

05:21.782 --> 05:24.406
He delights to show himself powerful in your life.

05:24.706 --> 05:25.948
He delights to heal.

05:26.188 --> 05:27.771
He delights to provide.

05:27.791 --> 05:29.293
He delights to answer prayer.

05:29.593 --> 05:31.576
He delights to strengthen your marriage.

05:31.596 --> 05:33.439
He delights to strengthen your children.

05:33.719 --> 05:35.622
He delights to touch your finances.

05:35.902 --> 05:37.745
He delights to work in your life.

05:37.765 --> 05:39.787
He delights to heal your emotions.

05:40.088 --> 05:41.650
He's a good God.

05:43.490 --> 05:44.371
And he does good.

05:44.431 --> 05:46.293
It's like that song.

05:47.054 --> 05:51.379
God is good all the time and all the time.

05:51.419 --> 05:53.641
There you go.

05:54.262 --> 05:55.483
He is good.

05:56.104 --> 06:02.871
Number two, recognize the goodness of God in his gifts.

06:02.891 --> 06:13.202
I think it's very, very important for you and I to take to heart what the Psalmist says in Psalm 103, bless the Lord, oh my soul, and all that is within me, bless his holy name,

06:13.986 --> 06:19.955
Bless the Lord, oh my soul, verse two, and forget not any of his benefits.

06:22.098 --> 06:30.490
One of the things that causes people to fall into temptation, Dietrich Bonhoeffer said, it's not that they hate God, it's just they forget about God.

06:32.333 --> 06:38.622
They forget not only about God, but they forget about the things that God has done in their life, the way God has provided.

06:38.683 --> 06:43.730
And so James says, James chapter one and verse 17, every good,

06:44.354 --> 06:48.121
And every perfect gift is from above.

06:49.785 --> 06:54.734
You and I don't have anything that's coming to our life that's good and perfect that God didn't give us.

06:55.797 --> 06:58.362
If you got a good job, that came from God.

06:59.504 --> 07:02.991
If you've got a good home, that came from God.

07:03.071 --> 07:06.738
If you got a good marriage, that came from God.

07:07.746 --> 07:11.831
He who finds a good wife finds a good thing and receives favor from the Lord.

07:11.851 --> 07:13.253
That's what the Bible says, right?

07:13.634 --> 07:15.156
I got a good wife.

07:15.416 --> 07:17.118
She's a gift from God, right?

07:18.400 --> 07:19.542
I got good kids.

07:19.842 --> 07:21.164
They're a gift from God.

07:22.666 --> 07:27.012
I've got grand grandchildren and they are a gift from God.

07:27.032 --> 07:33.861
I pastor a good church and you are a gift from God.

07:33.981 --> 07:34.802
You are.

07:37.506 --> 07:41.350
We've got great worship, and that's a gift from God.

07:42.932 --> 07:45.655
We've got great people leading our youth ministry.

07:45.915 --> 07:47.177
That's a gift from God.

07:47.617 --> 07:52.442
We've got great people leading our kids ministry, and that's a great gift from God.

07:52.462 --> 07:57.048
If you've got a great life group, that's a great gift from God, right?

07:58.549 --> 08:01.252
If you're on a dream team, it's a good dream team.

08:01.613 --> 08:03.395
That's a good gift from God.

08:04.015 --> 08:06.578
Every good, and every

08:06.658 --> 08:10.383
Perfect gift is from God.

08:10.844 --> 08:15.270
Nothing happens in your life apart from God.

08:16.913 --> 08:21.479
And notice he sends good and he sends what he sends is perfect.

08:22.801 --> 08:28.269
In other words, God knows not only what you need, he knows when you need it.

08:29.892 --> 08:30.853
Settle it in your heart.

08:30.953 --> 08:34.418
He is a good, good God.

08:34.978 --> 08:41.445
And the fact you've received those good and those perfect gifts is not due to luck.

08:43.707 --> 08:45.650
It's not due to your ability.

08:47.111 --> 08:49.974
If you have ability, that's a gift from God.

08:50.515 --> 08:53.498
If you add opportunity, that's a gift from God.

08:53.538 --> 09:00.165
If you were at the right time, at the right place, that perfect timing, every good and perfect gift is from God, right?

09:00.245 --> 09:04.530
You know, everything we have is from God.

09:05.730 --> 09:07.772
Got a good car, it's a gift from God.

09:09.314 --> 09:11.177
Got a loud truck, it's a gift from God.

09:15.682 --> 09:22.290
Every good and perfect gift is from God and it's God's character on display in your life.

09:23.932 --> 09:27.156
It's God showing you, you know, a lot of times people forget what God has done.

09:28.898 --> 09:31.341
And when you forget what God's done, you forget that he's good.

09:32.662 --> 09:35.666
This is why it's very, very important to maintain if you're gonna,

09:35.746 --> 09:42.617
If you're gonna overcome temptation, if you're gonna stay away from temptation, the first thing you gotta have is a thankful heart that remembers the goodness of God.

09:44.079 --> 09:45.421
He is a good God.

09:45.882 --> 09:51.450
His posture toward his people is always one of giving, not withholding.

09:53.213 --> 09:58.261
And would you notice his gifts, every good and perfect gift, is from above.

09:59.663 --> 10:00.905
So it all came from God.

10:02.367 --> 10:04.370
If you have it, it's because God gave it to you.

10:06.178 --> 10:11.206
And not only did it come, but would you notice it's coming down from the Father?

10:11.587 --> 10:13.169
In other words, it's present tense.

10:13.229 --> 10:19.138
So it's like God is constantly sending another gift your way.

10:20.941 --> 10:26.450
That answer, that thing you need, he knows what you need, he knows when you need it, he's sending it down.

10:28.418 --> 10:29.840
every good and perfect gift.

10:29.860 --> 10:31.182
In fact, I would go beyond this.

10:31.483 --> 10:36.490
He not only knows what you need, but he knows what you'd like, and if it's good for you, it's coming down.

10:38.573 --> 10:47.206
How many know God goes beyond what we, I mean, God could do a lot less for a lot of us, and we'd have what we need, right?

10:49.009 --> 10:52.815
But he's the God who delights in blessing us.

10:54.578 --> 10:57.522
There's nothing wrong with blessing as long as

10:57.666 --> 11:01.011
We don't get our eyes on the blessing instead of the God who blesses.

11:03.214 --> 11:06.078
Nothing wrong with having things as long as things don't have you.

11:07.840 --> 11:20.899
You gotta keep things in perspective and a thankful heart is the key to that and recognizing where those things came from and that those things are gifts from God and even though he gives them to us, we are only stewards of them.

11:21.199 --> 11:23.282
They do not belong to us.

11:23.362 --> 11:27.067
they are alone to us and we steward those things in our life.

11:27.387 --> 11:36.418
And the proof of that is that many, the material things, especially, you don't take them with you to heaven.

11:36.438 --> 11:41.264
Now there are gifts that God gives us that are in us.

11:43.267 --> 11:52.178
And I would suggest as well, as we think about these things, don't only think of the external things, think of the internal things that God has gifted you with.

11:52.674 --> 11:54.636
If you have an ability, he gave that to you.

11:54.656 --> 11:57.259
If you have the ability to teach, he gave that to you.

11:57.560 --> 12:00.563
If you have the ability to be a craftsman, he gave that to you.

12:02.545 --> 12:07.290
If you have the ability to sell, he gave that to you.

12:07.911 --> 12:17.522
If you have the ability to counsel somebody and help somebody, he gave that to you.

12:17.698 --> 12:22.305
science and medicine came easy to you and was interesting to you.

12:22.565 --> 12:23.667
That's a gift from God.

12:23.687 --> 12:24.528
That's not just you.

12:24.608 --> 12:25.389
That's him.

12:25.690 --> 12:27.532
He gave that to you.

12:27.813 --> 12:29.034
He gives gifts.

12:29.054 --> 12:32.399
And then along with that, there are gifts that you and I have within us.

12:32.780 --> 12:36.886
Many times we are not aware of until God calls them forth from within us.

12:37.927 --> 12:45.458
If he gives you the gift to lead, if he gives you the gift to serve, if he gives you the gift of hospitality, what an amazing gift.

12:47.202 --> 12:51.267
That's not just because your mom taught you, praise God for your mom, she was a gift.

12:53.410 --> 13:07.467
But then God put a gift in you and that's that gift to be able to host and to be hospitable and praise God for people who have that ability or the ability to encourage.

13:09.310 --> 13:12.494
I mean, there are all kinds of gifts that God gives.

13:13.235 --> 13:16.018
Well, number three, rest

13:16.162 --> 13:20.386
in the goodness of God and his unchanging character.

13:22.628 --> 13:25.011
God is consistently good.

13:26.712 --> 13:31.757
He is good all the time, which means, A.W.

13:31.777 --> 13:38.624
Tozer said, the goodness of God means that he does the greatest amount of good for the greatest number of people for the longest period of time.

13:40.465 --> 13:45.170
And when we say he is good all the time and his unchanging character,

13:45.378 --> 13:49.785
The theologians call that unchanging nature, his immutability, God does not change.

13:50.706 --> 13:52.609
Which is a wonderful thing for us.

13:53.050 --> 13:56.836
Jesus Christ the same yesterday, today, and forever.

13:56.856 --> 13:58.018
You wanna know what Jesus is like?

13:58.038 --> 13:58.839
Read the Gospels.

13:59.140 --> 14:02.265
Because he's still the same Jesus today as he was then.

14:02.705 --> 14:04.087
He is still the same.

14:04.368 --> 14:05.670
He is still gentle.

14:05.950 --> 14:07.112
He is still loving.

14:07.373 --> 14:08.514
He is still kind.

14:08.795 --> 14:09.957
He is still a healer.

14:10.277 --> 14:13.362
He is still the great teacher.

14:14.050 --> 14:17.694
And the great shepherd, he's the same.

14:19.316 --> 14:26.785
And the father of lights, when it says he is the every good and perfect gift, he's from above, coming down from the father of lights.

14:26.825 --> 14:27.747
He's full of lights.

14:28.868 --> 14:33.093
And that awesome light, live truth.

14:34.915 --> 14:41.463
And he's dependable with whom there's no variation or shadow due to change.

14:41.483 --> 14:43.826
So he doesn't change with the time of day.

14:45.090 --> 14:51.157
He doesn't say, well, you know, it's into the day I'm a little tired, so come back tomorrow.

14:51.177 --> 14:55.842
He doesn't say, well, you know, I used to do that for people, but I'm tired of doing it for people because they don't appreciate it.

14:58.705 --> 15:00.067
He doesn't, people change.

15:02.069 --> 15:14.002
I mean, your circumstances can change, your attitude can change, your opinions can change, your desires can change, your emotions can change, but God's goodness never changes.

15:14.178 --> 15:17.721
He is the same, always the same.

15:18.062 --> 15:24.948
What he said in his word is as true today as it was back then, and it will be true a hundred thousand years into eternity.

15:27.551 --> 15:31.594
Never gonna change, never gonna get up and find out God's decided to change the rules.

15:33.076 --> 15:33.656
It's the same.

15:35.458 --> 15:40.483
And God has purposed that he would demonstrate his goodness to us.

15:42.024 --> 15:43.986
You know, it's interesting when

15:45.218 --> 15:52.827
When Moses says to the Lord, and I don't have it, it just comes to my mind, but I think it's interesting relative to the goodness of God.

15:53.227 --> 15:56.471
When Moses says, show me your glory.

15:57.993 --> 16:12.690
Such an interesting thing to me because Moses has watched God do some incredible things, and Moses has spent 40 days on the Mount with God, and Moses and the elders of Israel have had a banquet

16:12.962 --> 16:15.926
with the living God, with the preincarnate Jesus Christ.

16:17.028 --> 16:18.450
I mean, he's had some encounters.

16:18.831 --> 16:26.201
He's spit in the glory of God so much that his face literally glows with the glory of God.

16:27.924 --> 16:34.774
So you would think that when Moses is saying, show me your glory that God would say, well, you know, Moses, I've already done that.

16:34.834 --> 16:36.016
I mean, what more do you want?

16:37.718 --> 16:39.541
But God says, I will be happy to.

16:40.843 --> 16:42.866
Do you realize God's happy to show you his glory?

16:43.266 --> 16:49.935
He's happy to reveal Himself to us in His presence.

16:49.956 --> 16:51.077
I think that's just such a way.

16:51.378 --> 16:53.901
God is happy to show you who He is.

16:54.883 --> 16:58.408
So when Moses asks that, God says, okay, you can't see my face.

16:58.448 --> 16:59.509
That's the only thing you can't do.

16:59.970 --> 17:02.994
But I'm going to pass by.

17:03.298 --> 17:12.327
And when I pass by, you'll be able to see my glory, and I'm gonna cover you in a rock, so with my hand, so when I go by, you'll see the afterglow of my glory.

17:12.607 --> 17:14.669
But as God passes by, what happens?

17:15.110 --> 17:20.395
There is a shout, the Lord gracious and compassionate.

17:21.636 --> 17:26.882
Slow to anger, listen to this, abounding in loving kindness or goodness.

17:29.004 --> 17:30.045
What's God's glory?

17:30.125 --> 17:31.186
How does God

17:31.426 --> 17:32.528
see His glory.

17:32.788 --> 17:37.537
He sees His glory as His loving kindness and His goodness extended to people.

17:39.039 --> 17:39.881
Isn't that beautiful?

17:41.303 --> 17:46.432
That should tell you right there, God delights in doing good to people.

17:46.452 --> 17:52.082
What happens though, a lot of people put roadblocks in their life and when a person walks

17:52.162 --> 18:02.662
in unrighteousness, when they walk in impurity, when they walk in unbelief, when they walk in selfishness, when they walk in the flesh, when they believe the lie of the enemy.

18:03.022 --> 18:15.666
What happens is it diminishes by their own action, the ability of God to work in their life to the degree he would want to.

18:18.338 --> 18:23.086
God wants to work in your life in ways you can't begin to imagine he is good.

18:23.867 --> 18:25.369
Give you three scriptures we'll close here.

18:26.571 --> 18:29.876
Give thanks to the Lord for he is good.

18:29.937 --> 18:30.618
Watch this.

18:31.279 --> 18:34.504
His love endures forever.

18:35.365 --> 18:35.846
Wow.

18:37.008 --> 18:40.934
He's good and he's good forever.

18:40.974 --> 18:44.540
The demonstration of his love is forever.

18:44.560 --> 18:45.842
Psalm 34 verse eight.

18:46.786 --> 18:50.771
Taste and see that the Lord is good.

18:52.553 --> 18:55.517
Blessed is the man who takes refuge in him.

18:57.459 --> 18:58.981
But just take a taste.

19:00.964 --> 19:02.766
Just try it.

19:03.047 --> 19:06.972
Some of you have not yet tried the goodness of God.

19:08.453 --> 19:08.934
He's good.

19:09.355 --> 19:11.037
He's better than you can imagine.

19:11.697 --> 19:15.282
He's more wonderful.

19:15.522 --> 19:18.085
and more good in our life than you and I deserve.

19:18.385 --> 19:23.430
See, here's the thing, a lot of people, and this is another one of the lives of the enemy, he says, well, you don't deserve that.

19:24.371 --> 19:38.886
As I'm talking about the goodness of God, some of you are having this internal conversation, and it's very likely the enemy trying to do what he did in the garden, that's causing not to trust God, not to look to God, and he's saying, you don't deserve that.

19:38.986 --> 19:39.207
Why?

19:39.807 --> 19:41.389
I mean, come on, look at your life.

19:41.529 --> 19:42.610
Why would God help you?

19:44.674 --> 19:45.715
Why would God show you?

19:45.795 --> 19:46.396
You heard him.

19:46.436 --> 19:51.681
He said, if you're not righteous, you're not pure, then you've diminished the goodness of God.

19:51.701 --> 19:54.764
So see, you don't have any reason to expect God to do anything for you.

19:56.645 --> 19:58.828
But the Psalmist says, taste and see, he's good.

19:59.889 --> 20:03.052
I think tonight's the night where God wants to show his goodness to people.

20:03.452 --> 20:09.438
I believe that when you and I are in the presence of the Lord and the Word of God is going forward, it tells us what God wants to do.

20:11.360 --> 20:13.842
And tonight God wants to show you his goodness.

20:14.498 --> 20:15.880
And I don't care where you've come from.

20:16.200 --> 20:17.222
I don't care what you've done.

20:17.522 --> 20:19.405
Tonight God wants to show you His goodness.

20:19.705 --> 20:21.107
God wants to show you is real.

20:21.348 --> 20:22.830
He wants to show you He's there.

20:25.153 --> 20:35.227
One of the things I like to do it in every now and then with people is just say, when they tell me they don't believe in God, I just like to say, well, what is it that you're facing in your life that I could pray with you about?

20:35.868 --> 20:39.954
And if God answered our prayer, you would know He's real.

20:43.842 --> 20:45.584
I mean, let's do it.

20:47.005 --> 20:49.668
And just let God show Himself powerful.

20:49.728 --> 20:51.210
He delights to do it.

20:52.872 --> 20:55.455
Nahum, one-seven, Nahum.

20:55.495 --> 20:59.959
Not a book many people read, but a book that's got some good promises in it.

21:00.380 --> 21:01.101
The Lord is good.

21:02.502 --> 21:04.344
A refuge in times of trouble.

21:04.985 --> 21:07.387
He cares for those who trust in Him.

21:07.407 --> 21:08.829
You just say, God, I trust you.

21:09.109 --> 21:09.810
